
[1]loll

   LOLL, v.i. [The sense of this word is to throw, to send. Hence it
   coincides with the Gr..]

   1. To recline; to lean; properly, to throw one's self down; hence, to
   lie at ease.

   Void of care he lolls supine in state.

   2. To suffer the tongue to hang extended from the mouth, as an ox or a
   dog when heated with labor or exertion.

   The triple porter of the Stygian seat, with lolling tongue lay fawning
   at his feet.

                  LOLL, v.t. To thrust out, as the tongue.

   Fierce tigers couched around, and lolled their tongues.
